getBitSets

public java.util.BitSet[] getBitSets()
Specified by:
getBitSets in interface CategoryMapper
Returns:
An array of BitSets representing the categories. So BitSet no. i is a set of all elements contained in group i. So if there is a one at position j in BitSet i the element j is contained in group i. The names can be mapped back with getKeyName(j) and getGroupName(j).
